 women's hockey areall on the menufor Team SA at the Paris Olympics on Saturday.\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 520, \"end\": 522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5472313656873515e-28, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ATHLETICS  Men's 1500m repechage (7.15pm):Tshepo Tshite  Men's 1500m repechage (7.26pm):Ryan Mphahlele  Men's 100m, first round, heats:Shaun Maswangani, Benjamin Richardson, Akani Simbine  CYCLING  Men's road race (11am):Ryan Gibbons  GOLF  Men's Individual, third round  10.11am:Christiaan Bezuidenhout  12.06pm:Erik van Rooyen  HOCKEY  Women's Pool B (1.15pm):Team SA vs United States  ROWING  Women's single scull, C final (9.30am):Paige Badenhorst  Akani Simbineisone of the favouritesin the men's 100m sprint, and there is a massive extra incentive that does make for interesting reading.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 712, \"end\": 720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.9995541025381988, \"rank\": 0.00029303529976415363, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9994574392643352, \"rank\": 0.0005428546456094197, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 733, \"end\": 746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}, {\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christiaan_Bezuidenhout\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christiaan Bezuidenhout\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christiaan_Bezuidenhout\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christiaan_Bezuidenhout\"}, {\"begin\": 872, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erik_van_Rooyen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Erik van Rooyen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erik_van_Rooyen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erik_van_Rooyen\"}, {\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5472313656873515e-28, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier this year,World Athleticsannouncedit will become the first international federation to award prize money at anOlympics.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medal winners in each of the 48 athletics events in Paris will receive$50 000 (R915 000).\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999122338, \"rank\": 8.760149518951888e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The total prize fund of $2.4 million will come from the International Olympic Committee's revenue share allocation that World Athletics receives every four years.\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1434, \"end\": 1465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1498, \"end\": 1513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999919004949, \"rank\": 8.099442660770025e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each individual Olympic champion will receive $50 000 and relay teams will receive the same amount, to be shared among the team members.\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Along with the Team SA bonus of R400 000, if Simbine could also clinch the R915 000 up for grabs from World Athletics, he could ultimately bank just over R1.3 million if he grabs gold.\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1699, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5472313656873515e-28, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999919004949, \"rank\": 8.099442660770025e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That would be more than triple any other single gold medal winner from Team SA who are not part of the athletics team.\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1940, \"end\": 1942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5472313656873515e-28, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anything less than gold, though, and the athletics duo will only be in line for the Sascoc incentives as World Athletics prize money will only be paid to the winners of silver and bronze medals from the 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2089, \"end\": 2104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999919004949, \"rank\": 8.099442660770025e-09, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 2204, \"end\": 2215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999917625535129, \"rank\": 8.203578164570433e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring!\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2218, \"end\": 2221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"score\": 0.999998692451245, \"rank\": 1.1823403370853127e-06, \"text\": \"WIN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\"}, {\"begin\": 2222, \"end\": 2224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\", \"score\": 0.9857812516369202, \"rank\": 0.014415642756793412, \"tex